ent elementor-element-8924109 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8924109\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Who are you?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4a061d4 elementor-align-center elementor-widget__width-auto elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"4a061d4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-sm\" href=\"\/family-application\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">I'm a Parent...<\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2e516fd elementor-align-center elementor-widget__width-auto elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"2e516fd\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-sm\" href=\"\/candidate-application\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">I'm a Nanny...<\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d216756 elementor-align-center elementor-widget__width-auto elementor-widget-mobile__width-inherit elementor-widget-tablet__width-inherit elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"d216756\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-sm\" href=\"#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dpopup%3Aopen%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6IjMzOTgiLCJ0b2dnbGUiOmZhbHNlfQ%3D%3D\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Other Inquiry<\/span>\n\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-7e5f8d66 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"7e5f8d66\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b5bfbf0\" data-id=\"b5bfbf0\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-356c24f2 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"356c24f2\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">In the Meantime<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5573a7a elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"5573a7a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Parenting is full of questions\u2026<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-67894244 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"67894244\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Thankfully, we have some of the answers.<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1624aa89 elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-3394 elementor-widget-accordion\" data-id=\"1624aa89\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"accordion.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3711\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"1\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3711\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">\u200b\u200bIf my nanny calls out sick, do you offer backup care?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3711\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"1\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3711\"><p>Our focus at NBN is to provide your long-term solution but we can point you in the right direction for backup care should you need it.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3712\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3712\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">How does your replacement policy work?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3712\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"2\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3712\"><p>Even in a perfect placement, the unexpected can arise. Our 90-day credit replacement policy for permanent hires is there for you in that event. We will do all we can to provide a suitable replacement candidate should you need to terminate employment or the nanny resigns her position.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3713\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3713\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">What are your placement fees?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3713\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3713\"><p>Bespoke placement is both time and labor intensive. We charge a one-time, non-refundable $400 engagement fee to initiate your search.<\/p><ul><li>Live-out Placement &#8211; 15% of nanny\u2019s gross annual earnings for long-term (3+ months).<\/li><li>Live-in Placement &#8211; 20% of nanny\u2019s gross annual earnings for long-term (3+ months).<\/li><li>Temporary Hires &#8211; 25% of nanny\u2019s gross earnings for the employment period covered (1\u20133 months).<\/li><li>Newborn Care &#8211; 25% of the NCS\u2019s gross earnings for the employment period covered.<\/li><\/ul><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3714\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"4\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3714\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">What are typical nanny rates?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3714\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"4\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3714\"><p>Hourly rates in NYC vary greatly based on experience, education, special skills, additional languages, and each position\u2019s level of responsibility. Given the caliber of candidates we represent, we typically see gross hourly rates of $30-$35+ per hour.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3715\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"5\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3715\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">My friend pays her sitter $25\/hr. Why are your rates higher?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3715\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"5\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3715\"><p>There are some common misconceptions about what a sitter can offer and the gifts and support a great nanny will bring to your family. To better understand the differences, please see our <a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/Babysitter-vs.-Nanny-10.2020-3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Babysitter vs. Nanny Resource Sheet<\/a>.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3716\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"6\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3716\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">How do I pay my nanny?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3716\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"6\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3716\"><p>The nanny is your employee; therefore, you are responsible for all applicable taxes and withholdings. Nannies are paid an hourly rate and receive their compensation weekly. As the employer, you pay the nanny directly. We do not take any part of the nanny\u2019s compensation.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3717\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"7\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3717\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">Can I pay my nanny under the table?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3717\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"7\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3717\"><p>If your childcare provider earns in excess of your state&#8217;s annual earnings threshold for tax withholdings, you are required by Federal law to withhold taxes by filing a W2. Not doing so puts your family at risk of serious legal implications. Let us put you in touch with our payroll partners at GTM to keep your family safe, and your nanny receiving professional legal employment.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3718\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"8\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3718\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">Do I have to pay my nanny\u2019s taxes?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3718\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"8\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3718\"><p>Every family who decides to hire a nanny is responsible for any applicable tax, withholding, and reporting. Please see <a href=\"https:\/\/gtm.com\/household\/nannies-by-noa\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tax &amp; Payroll Services<\/a> to find information on your tax obligations as a domestic employer.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-3719\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"9\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-3719\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">Where do you find your nannies?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-3719\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"9\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-3719\"><p>Great Nannies often come our way via word of mouth referrals, many return to us as their contract term ends and they seek new employment and others we source through a variety of well-established industry resources and job boards. In the end though, wherever we meet candidates, they must all go through the exact same recruitment and evaluation process- every time!<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-37110\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"10\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-37110\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">How do you screen your nannies?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-37110\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"10\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-37110\"><p>All applicants are screened in an in-depth 3-part interview process, with 3 individual team members to gain a broad perspective of skills, professionalism, knowledge, communication, acceptance of feedback, and the desired demeanor for childcare.<\/p><p>We speak with and cross-reference, a minimum of 2 previous employers to assess past performance (Past performance is the best indicator of future performance). Along with public social media reviews. <\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-37111\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"11\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-37111\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">When do you run background checks and what do you check?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-37111\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"11\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-37111\"><p>We know safety is your priority; It\u2019s ours too. Our background checks are the most comprehensive available in our industry. We check to a federal level: identity research, multijurisdictional criminal records database, county-of-residence criminal research, state level criminal record and sex offender research, federal district criminal research.<\/p><p>A la carte options are also available upon request such as: education verification, employment history, CPO\u2019s (civil protective orders) international criminal checks, and 10-panel drug screening. Need a check that you don\u2019t see listed? Just ask!<\/p><p>Due to NYC\u2019s \u2018Fair Chance Act\u2019, we are no longer able to run or disclose any criminal background check information, including motor vehicle checks (in NYC) on any applicant prior to receipt of an accepted, conditional offer of employment.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-37112\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"12\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-37112\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">What benefits should I provide my nanny?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-37112\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"12\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-37112\"><p>What is mandated by law vs. what\u2019s the industry standard? We\u2019ll walk you through this step by step during your consultation call so you can customize a compensation package that incentivizes top talent and fits your budget. In general, nannies seek 2 weeks of annual paid vacation, sick\/ personal days, major federal holidays and commuter\/ travel stipends. Families sometimes offer Health Insurance packages or stipends. Talk to us about a tax-free health care reimbursement for your nanny- it\u2019s a valuable incentive!<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-accordion-item\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h4 id=\"elementor-tab-title-37113\" class=\"elementor-tab-title\" data-tab=\"13\" role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-37113\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-accordion-title\" tabindex=\"0\">Are you insured?<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-37113\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"13\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-37113\"><p>We are licensed by the Department of Consumer Affairs (license # 2017000-DCA) and are bonded and insured.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<script type=\"application\/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https:\\\/\\\/schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"\\u200b\\u200bIf my nanny calls out sick, do you offer backup care?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Our focus at NBN is to provide your long-term solution but we can point you in the right direction for backup care should you need it.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How does your replacement policy work?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Even in a perfect placement, the unexpected can arise. Our 90-day credit replacement policy for permanent hires is there for you in that event. We will do all we can to provide a suitable replacement candidate should you need to terminate employment or the nanny resigns her position.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are your placement fees?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Bespoke placement is both time and labor intensive. We charge a one-time, non-refundable $400 engagement fee to initiate your search.<\\\/p><ul><li>Live-out Placement &#8211; 15% of nanny\\u2019s gross annual earnings for long-term (3+ months).<\\\/li><li>Live-in Placement &#8211; 20% of nanny\\u2019s gross annual earnings for long-term (3+ months).<\\\/li><li>Temporary Hires &#8211; 25% of nanny\\u2019s gross earnings for the employment period covered (1\\u20133 months).<\\\/li><li>Newborn Care &#8211; 25% of the NCS\\u2019s gross earnings for the employment period covered.<\\\/li><\\\/ul>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are typical nanny rates?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Hourly rates in NYC vary greatly based on experience, education, special skills, additional languages, and each position\\u2019s level of responsibility. Given the caliber of candidates we represent, we typically see gross hourly rates of $30-$35+ per hour.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"My friend pays her sitter $25\\\/hr. Why are your rates higher?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>There are some common misconceptions about what a sitter can offer and the gifts and support a great nanny will bring to your family. To better understand the differences, please see our <a href=\\\"\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2022\\\/06\\\/Babysitter-vs.-Nanny-10.2020-3.pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\">Babysitter vs. Nanny Resource Sheet<\\\/a>.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do I pay my nanny?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>The nanny is your employee; therefore, you are responsible for all applicable taxes and withholdings. Nannies are paid an hourly rate and receive their compensation weekly. As the employer, you pay the nanny directly. We do not take any part of the nanny\\u2019s compensation.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I pay my nanny under the table?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>If your childcare provider earns in excess of your state&#8217;s annual earnings threshold for tax withholdings, you are required by Federal law to withhold taxes by filing a W2. Not doing so puts your family at risk of serious legal implications. Let us put you in touch with our payroll partners at GTM to keep your family safe, and your nanny receiving professional legal employment.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do I have to pay my nanny\\u2019s taxes?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Every family who decides to hire a nanny is responsible for any applicable tax, withholding, and reporting. Please see <a href=\\\"https:\\\/\\\/gtm.com\\\/household\\\/nannies-by-noa\\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\">Tax &amp; Payroll Services<\\\/a> to find information on your tax obligations as a domestic employer.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where do you find your nannies?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>Great Nannies often come our way via word of mouth referrals, many return to us as their contract term ends and they seek new employment and others we source through a variety of well-established industry resources and job boards. In the end though, wherever we meet candidates, they must all go through the exact same recruitment and evaluation process- every time!<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you screen your nannies?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>All applicants are screened in an in-depth 3-part interview process, with 3 individual team members to gain a broad perspective of skills, professionalism, knowledge, communication, acceptance of feedback, and the desired demeanor for childcare.<\\\/p><p>We speak with and cross-reference, a minimum of 2 previous employers to assess past performance (Past performance is the best indicator of future performance). Along with public social media reviews. <\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"When do you run background checks and what do you check?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>We know safety is your priority; It\\u2019s ours too. Our background checks are the most comprehensive available in our industry. We check to a federal level: identity research, multijurisdictional criminal records database, county-of-residence criminal research, state level criminal record and sex offender research, federal district criminal research.<\\\/p><p>A la carte options are also available upon request such as: education verification, employment history, CPO\\u2019s (civil protective orders) international criminal checks, and 10-panel drug screening. Need a check that you don\\u2019t see listed? Just ask!<\\\/p><p>Due to NYC\\u2019s \\u2018Fair Chance Act\\u2019, we are no longer able to run or disclose any criminal background check information, including motor vehicle checks (in NYC) on any applicant prior to receipt of an accepted, conditional offer of employment.<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What benefits should I provide my nanny?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>What is mandated by law vs. what\\u2019s the industry standard? We\\u2019ll walk you through this step by step during your consultation call so you can customize a compensation package that incentivizes top talent and fits your budget. In general, nannies seek 2 weeks of annual paid vacation, sick\\\/ personal days, major federal holidays and commuter\\\/ travel stipends. Families sometimes offer Health Insurance packages or stipends. Talk to us about a tax-free health care reimbursement for your nanny- it\\u2019s a valuable incentive!<\\\/p>\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are you insured?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"<p>We are licensed by the Department of Consumer Affairs (license # 2017000-DCA) and are bonded and insured.<\\\/p>\"}}]}<\/script>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3ce8ee87 elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3ce8ee87\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-1c7f9d0d\" data-id=\"1c7f9d0d\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-158a1922 elementor-widget elementor-widget-template\" data-id=\"158a1922\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"template.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-template\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"section\" data-elementor-id=\"3380\" class=\"elementor elementor-3380\" data-elementor-post-type=\"elementor_library\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-72a180c4 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"72a180c4\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-33bae105\" data-id